<a name="top" class="anchor"></a><div id="contentObp" class="main"><div id="topnav"></div>


<p class="info-box warning">For Aged Care skill tagged staff only.</p>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_L3TT_Manual_adjustme"></a>
<h3>Manual adjustment calculations for pre 1 July 2014 residential care recipients</h3>


<p>This table contains information on how to complete a manual adjustment for a care recipient receiving residential care under the pre 1 July 2014 scheme.</p>
<table caption="This table contains information on how to complete a manual adjustment for a care recipient receiving residential care under the pre 1 July 2014 scheme." class="" width="100%">
<tr>
<td width="11%">
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step"></a>
<p><strong>Step</strong></p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Action</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step01"></a>
<p>1</p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Determine if the means assessment is correct</strong> <a title="Read more 1" class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step01" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;"><span class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step01" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;">+</span> Read more ...</a></p>
<div class="showcont">


<p>Before starting the manual adjustment process, the means assessment (MA) and ongoing Income Tested Fee (ITF) must be correct and accurately reflect the care recipient's current circumstances.</p>

<p>In the <strong>Aged Care Staff Portal</strong> (<strong>ACSP</strong>), check&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
<strong>Fees and charges</strong> &gt; <strong>Fees and charges details</strong> for fee information</li>
		<li>
<strong>Means Testing</strong> &gt; <strong>Means testing current summary</strong> for total income</li>
		</ul>
<p>Is the current care recipient means information in ACSP correct?</p>
		<ul>		<li>
<strong>Yes</strong>, <a href="../older-australians/065-20010631-03.html#bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step02">go to Step 2</a></li>
		<li>
<strong>No</strong>, remediation is required to correct the means assessment. For more information, see <a href="../older-australians/065-20082042-01.html">Aged care reviews - reassessments and updates</a>. Procedure ends here</li>		</ul>
</div>


<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step02"></a>
<p>2</p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Determine if the ongoing fee is correct</strong> <a title="Read more 2" class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step02" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;"><span class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step02" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;">+</span> Read more ...</a></p>
<div class="showcont">


<p>Is the ongoing ITF correct?</p>
		<ul>		<li>
<strong>Yes</strong>, a manual adjustment is required. <a href="../older-australians/065-20010631-03.html#bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step03">Go to Step 3</a></li>
		<li>
<strong>No</strong>, an ad hoc review is required. For more information, see <a href="../older-australians/065-20063010-01.html">Aged care reviews - ad hoc reviews</a>. Procedure ends here</li>		</ul>
</div>


<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step03"></a>
<p>3</p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Determine the start date of manual adjustment calculation</strong> <a title="Read more 3" class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step03" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;"><span class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step03" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;">+</span> Read more ...</a></p>
<div class="showcont">


<p>In <strong>ACSP</strong>&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
check <strong>Care recipient</strong> &gt; <strong>Care recipient summary</strong> for entry and departure events. See <a href="../older-australians/065-22040400-01.html">Aged Care Staff Portal (ACSP) â€“ Care Recipient in Context (CRiC)</a> for the process</li>
		<li>
note the following&#58;</li>
			<ul>			<li>
RACS ID</li>
			<li>
NAPS ID</li>
			<li>
Centrelink and/or DVA IDs (if present)</li>
			<li>
service name</li>
			<li>
date of entry (or pre-entry)</li>
			<li>
departure date (if applicable)</li>		</ul>
		<li>
a separate adjustment calculation is required where there has been a change in service providers</li>		</ul>
</div>


<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step04"></a>
<p>4</p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Determine marital status</strong> <a title="Read more 4" class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step04" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;"><span class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step04" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;">+</span> Read more ...</a></p>
<div class="showcont">


<p>In <strong>ACSP</strong>&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
navigate to <strong>Means Testing </strong>&gt;<strong> Circumstance</strong> for current and historical circumstances</li>
		<li>
check to confirm the marital status applicable to the adjustment period</li>
		</ul>
<p>In the Aged Care Fee Calculator&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
on the <strong>Manual Adjustment Calculator</strong> tab, key the marital status for each adjustment period</li>		</ul>
</div>


<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step05"></a>
<p>5</p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Determine income details</strong> <a title="Read more 5" class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step05" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;"><span class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step05" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;">+</span> Read more ...</a></p>
<div class="showcont">


<p>In <strong>ACSP</strong>&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
go to <strong>Means testing</strong> &gt; <strong>Total income</strong></li>
		<li>
for each adjustment period note the&#58;</li>
			<ul>			<li>
<strong>Date of effect</strong> (start date)</li>
			<li>
<strong>Created on </strong>date</li>
			<li>
<strong>Income Amount</strong></li>
			</ul>			</ul>
<p>Where more than one line relates to the adjustment period, note the above details for each line.</p>

<p><strong>Note&#58;</strong> use the most recently updated income. Do not use <strong>Superseded</strong> details.</p>

<p>In the <a href="../older-australians/065-20010631-05.html#bp05_L2GT_Calculator">Aged Care Fee Calculator</a>&#58;</p>

<p>For each adjustment period, key into the Manual Adjustment Calculator tab&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
start date</li>
		<li>
end date</li>
		<li>
fortnightly income amount</li>		</ul>
</div>


<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step06"></a>
<p>6</p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Determine the ITF</strong> <a title="Read more 6" class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step06" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;"><span class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step06" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;">+</span> Read more ...</a></p>
<div class="showcont">


<p>In <strong>ACSP</strong>&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
select <strong>Fees and charges </strong>&gt; <strong>Fees and charges details</strong></li>
		<li>
under <strong>Fees</strong>, confirm <strong>Income Tested Fee</strong> (ITF) amounts</li>
		<li>
select the arrow under <strong>Fee Type</strong> to sort fee types together<strong> </strong></li>
		</ul>
<p>In the <a href="../older-australians/065-20010631-05.html#bp05_L2GT_Calculator">Aged Care Fee Calculator</a>&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
open the <strong>Manual Adjustment Calculator</strong> tab</li>
		<li>
key the ITF for each adjustment period</li>		</ul>
</div>


<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step07"></a>
<p>7</p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Check if a refund has already paid for the same adjustment period</strong> <a title="Read more 7" class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step07" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;"><span class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step07" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;">+</span> Read more ...</a></p>
<div class="showcont">


<p>In <strong>ACSP</strong>&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
select <strong>Reconciliation</strong> &gt; <strong>Reviews and refunds</strong></li>
		<li>
review periods will be displayed for any previous reviews</li>
		<li>
select <strong>Review ID</strong> hyperlinks for details of review</li>
		<li>
if a refund is present for the same period as the manual adjustment, note the&#58;</li>
			<ul>			<li>
refund type</li>
			<li>
refund amount</li>
			<li>
dates the refund applies</li>
			<li>
the provider that received the refund</li>		</ul>
		<li>
check <strong>Fees and charges</strong> &gt; <strong>Fees and charges details</strong> for any previous hardship</li>
		<li>
check <strong>Care recipient</strong> &gt; <strong>Care recipient notes</strong> for any record of previously actioned manual adjustments </li>
		</ul>
<p>In <strong>System for the Payment of Residential Care</strong> (SPARC)&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
check <strong>Client Main Menu</strong> &gt; <strong>Client Notes</strong> for any historical manual adjustments that have been made</li>
		</ul>
<p>In <strong>Customer First</strong>&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
check Document List (<strong>DL</strong>) for any previously actioned manual adjustments or financial hardship assistance granted</li>
		<li>
where a refund has previously been paid for the same adjustment period, note the&#58;</li>
			<ul>			<li>
refund amount</li>
			<li>
dates the refund applies</li>			</ul>			</ul>
</div>


<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step08"></a>
<p>8</p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Calculate the correct fees</strong> <a title="Read more 8" class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step08" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;"><span class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step08" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;">+</span> Read more ...</a></p>
<div class="showcont">


<p>Use the <a href="../older-australians/065-20010631-05.html#bp05_L2GT_Calculator">Aged Care Fee Calculator</a> tab to calculate the correct ITF based on&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
assessable income for each period as identified in Step 5</li>
		<li>
a new calculation is required for each change in income, including Consumer Price Indexation (CPI) and threshold changes (occurring on 20 March, 1 July and 20 September)</li>
		<li>
<a href="../older-australians/065-20010631-03.html#bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step09">go to Step 9</a> to compare the calculated ITF against the advised ITF</li>		</ul>
</div>


<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step09"></a>
<p>9</p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Complete the manual adjustment calculation</strong> <a title="Read more 9" class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step09" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;"><span class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step09" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;">+</span> Read more ...</a></p>
<div class="showcont">


<p>Key the correct ITF (as calculated in Step 8) into the <strong>Manual Adjustment Calculator</strong> within the <a href="../older-australians/065-20010631-05.html#bp05_L2GT_Calculator">Aged Care Fee Calculator</a>&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
take into account refunds and/or manual adjustments previously issued</li>
		<li>
add the total amounts issued to the <strong>Less previous refunds issued</strong> field for each provider</li>
		<li>
the calculator advises if an ITF adjustment for the period is due</li>
		</ul>
<p>Manual Adjustment refunds do not pay if less than $1.00.</p>

<p>Check all <strong>Care Recipient Profile</strong> details are complete in the <strong>Manual Adjustment Calculator</strong>.</p>

<p>Scan and upload a copy of the calculations onto the Customer First record in PDF format via <strong>Document Tools</strong> using the <strong>Form Type</strong> of <strong>UNS005-Financial.</strong></p>
</div>


<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step10"></a>
<p>10</p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Create manual letter</strong> <a title="Read more 10" class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step10" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;"><span class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step10" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;">+</span> Read more ...</a></p>
<div class="showcont">


<p>Create a <a href="../older-australians/065-21052139-01.html">manual letter</a> using approved letter templates.</p>

<p>If the care recipient is deceased&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
do not issue a letter for a refund below $10</li>
		<li>
issue manual letters to the provider and the executor of the estate (if known) or the estate of the deceased</li>
		<li>
delegation to release information about a deceased person is at APS4 level</li>
		<li>
letters must be issued or approved by APS4 or above</li>
		</ul>
<p>Issue letters to&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
care recipient, or estate or executor of estate for deceased care recipients</li>
		<li>
aged care nominee (where applicable) in the aged care systems&#58;</li>
			<ul>			<li>
view nominee details in the <strong>Relationships</strong> in ACMPS</li>		</ul>
		<li>
service provider</li>		</ul>
</div>


<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step11"></a>
<p>11</p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Record action taken</strong> <a title="Read more 11" class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step11" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;"><span class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step11" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;">+</span> Read more ...</a></p>
<div class="showcont">


<p>Record the manual adjustment details via a <a href="../specialist-manuals-and-system-tools/111-05050020-03.html">Fast Note</a>. Use <strong>Fast Note</strong> - select <strong>Auto Text</strong>, use <strong>Aged Care </strong>&gt;<strong> Assessment </strong>&gt;<strong> Manual Adjustment - Res Care</strong>&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
in&#58;</li>
			<ul>			<li>
<strong>Text</strong>, complete the details required in each of the auto populated fields</li>
			<li>
<strong>Documents uploaded</strong>, insert <strong>Form Type&#58; UNS005 - Financial</strong></li>		</ul>
		<li>
if applicable, note that an email was sent to Payments Team including sent date. See Step 12</li>
		<li>
<strong>complete</strong> work item</li>
		</ul>
<p>In <strong>ACSP</strong>&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
go to <strong>Care recipient</strong> &gt; <strong>Care recipient notes</strong> </li>
		<li>
select <strong>Add Note</strong></li>
		<li>
<strong>Subject</strong>&#58; Manual Adjustment</li>
		<li>
add the following text&#58;</li>
			<ul>			<li>
Manual adjustment completed for period dd/mm/yy to dd/mm/yy. Care recipient may be due $xxx.xx. Payments Team emailed dd/mm/yy</li>		</ul>
		<li>
press <strong>Submit</strong></li>		</ul>
</div>


<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<a class="anchor" name="bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step12"></a>
<p>12</p></td>
<td>

<p><strong>Advise Payments team of manual adjustment calculated amount</strong> <a title="Read more 12" class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step12" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;"><span class="showhead bp03_tbl_Manual_adjustme_Step12" onclick="erefshow(this)" href="javascript:;">+</span> Read more ...</a></p>
<div class="showcont">


<p>The Aged Care Payments team is responsible for releasing care recipient refunds to providers. Smart Centres email refunds associated with QR in bulk with the subject of 'QR Refunds to be released'.</p>

<p>For all other refunds, send an email to the Payments Team with a copy to Aged Care Processing Team&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
subject title&#58;</li>
			<ul>			<li>
Refund to be released - ACSP ID, RACS ID, care recipient name</li>		</ul>
		<li>
text/body of email&#58;</li>
			<ul>			<li>
all relevant information relating to Fees</li>
			<li>
effective date and $ amount for ongoing ITF</li>
			<li>
BDF $ amount</li>
			<li>
refund period(s) and $ amount</li>			</ul>			</ul>
</div>


<p></p></td>
</tr>

